  "summary": "A broad traditional English-and-Hebrew Haggadah whose strongest value is a reliable ritual and narrative backbone; selected passages need OCR cleanup, beginner-facing action cues, and compassionate framing around violent or land-centered liturgy.",
  "sourceAssessment": {
    "voice": "Traditional, formal, explanatory, and prayer-centered, with a mid-century English register and substantial Hebrew embedded in the page extraction.",
    "bestUses": [
      "The core order and ritual-symbol explanations for a traditional-theme Haggadah",
      "A concise Exodus arc from ancestral migration through slavery, cry, and liberation",
      "Familiar praise, meal, and table ritual passages that can anchor a cohesive source-led edition"
    ],
    "beginnerRisks": [
      "The extraction contains broken Hebrew glyphs and layout artifacts that require visual comparison with the original pages.",
      "Some instructions assume that guests already know which object to lift, which cup to fill, and what action follows.",
      "Plague, firstborn, Temple, land, and Jerusalem passages need clear nontriumphalist or traditional-only gates."
    ],
    "politicalContext": "Biblical Israel, the land, Temple, and Jerusalem occur as traditional liturgy. The source also contains modern-sounding land refrains; the project may use a Jerusalem refrain only for a traditional selection without a social-justice override, and may not turn liturgy into exclusive modern political advocacy.",
